1.Decimal to 2's compliment: 1111 1111 0101 1110
2's compliment to hexadecimal: 0xFF5E

2.Hexadecimal to 2's compliment: 1111 1111 1010 0010
2's compliment to decimal: -94

3.convert 10.375 binary:1010.011
1.010011*2^3
127+3=130
130 to binary:1000 0010
IEEE floting point: 0100 0001 0010 0110 0000 0000 0000 0000
Convert 10.375 to single-precision IEEE floting point (hexadecimal) representation: 0x41260000

4.convert 0xC18E8000 binary:1100 0001 1000 1110 1000 0000 0000 0000
binary to decimal:1000 0011 = 131
127-131=4
-(2^4*1.00011101) = -(10001.1101)
binary to decimal: -17.8125
Convert 0xC18E8000 from single-precision IEEE floating point to decimal representation: -17.8125

